Test Case 1:

3D Center slot coater section

Ratio of inlet velocity to web speed of restart data : 0.95
Ratio of inlet velocity to web speed of current case : 0.94

Features:
Two material files are used.  They have identical fluid properties
but the psuedo solid shear modulus (Lame' mu) is three orders of
magnitude larger.  This material file is used in a region near
the static and dynamic contact lines to mititgate mesh distortion.

The dynamic contact line uses the VAR_CA_EDGE condition.  Since there
is no curvature to this DCL, there should be only one value of
contact applied along its length.  Using this condition, however,  does 
seem to improve robustness of converged

This test case exercises the VELO_NORMAL_EDGE, VELO_TANGENT_EDGE, CA_EDGE
and VAR_CA_EDGE conditions as well as the three dimensional rotation 
sections.

GMRES with ILU preconditioning is used as the linear solver.

Runtime on the compute server( sass2153) is roughly 30 minutes.

Five iterations to convergence should be expected.


Files:

input - 			input deck
newt.mat - 			material file for nominal psuedo-solid stiffness
stiff_newt.mat - 		material file for stiffer psuedo-solid
restart_center_slot3d.exoII - 	The exodus restart file 
solution_file.exoII - 		This is the exodus file created by goma containing the solution
output.txt - 			This is a text file echo the GOMA screen output for the run